          "name": "Claws of the Tyrant",
          "page": 24,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "*Nethys Note: This description was taken from the legacy entry of the monster.*    \n  \nA will-o'-wisp that starves to death might rise as a cold, blue, glowing sphere of spongy wetness\u2014a corpselight. A corpselight instinctively seeks out a host corpse to dwell within, as its physical form quickly deteriorates if not hidden within a dead creature.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
